["Karrharde (North Frisian: K\u00e5rhiird; Danish: K\u00e6r Herred) was an amt (collective municipality) in the district of Nordfriesland, in Schleswig-Holstein, Germany. It was situated on the border with Denmark, approx. 35\u00a0km north of Husum, and 25\u00a0km west of Flensburg. Its seat was in Leck, itself not part of the amt. In January 2008, it was merged with the \u00c4mter B\u00f6kingharde, S\u00fcderl\u00fcgum and Wiedingharde, and the municipalities Nieb\u00fcll and Leck to form the Amt S\u00fcdtondern.","The amt of Karrharde consisted of the following municipalities (as of 2005[update] population in parentheses):","This Nordfriesland location article is a stub. You can help Wikipedia by expanding it."]